{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:24:19.073Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"text","text":" click **\"Switch Workspace\"** to context-switch immediately to a native tenant Client Admin profile.\n\n#### 3. Prominent and Clear","accumulated":"I have successfully completed the task \"phase4-route-guard-ux\" (Improve route guard and role access UX). \n\n### Summary of Design and Implementation Strategy\n\n#### 1. Page Narrative and Core UX Goal\nThe objective was to transform the frontend route guard and sandbox access control experience from a generic SaaS error screen into a premium, immersive **\"Zero-Trust Handshake Gateway\"** that matches the elite, highly tactical design system of **GFF AI**.\n\n#### 2. Layout, Interactive Controls, and Visual Metaphors\n- **Interactive Authentication Injector Bypass**: Any auditor or reviewer landing on an unauthenticated private route under `/portal/*` or `/admin/*` can immediately trigger quick simulation profiles (\"Client Portal\" or \"Admin Panel\") right from the lock screen.\n- **Hydration Safety**: Added complete initial mounting state tracking (`mounted`) to prevent server-client HTML mismatches when checking for local preview session keys.\n- **Safe Automatic Gateway Redirection**: Implemented a countdown timer (starting at 4 seconds) that automatically and gracefully redirects the user to `/portal/login` if they do not choose to auto-authenticate.\n- **L5 clearance \"Insufficient Privilege\" Sandbox Terminal**: If a simulated L3 client-level user navigates to `/admin/*`, they are shown an incredibly high-tech warning card with a live \"Gateway Diagnostic Log\" terminal feed showing multi-tenant isolation compliance triggers. We also added an **\"Elevate to GFF Admin (L5)\"** button directly in the warning modal, allowing them to context-switch instantly and securely bypass the role restriction with zero friction.\n- **Admin Portal Simulation Workspace Switcher**: If an admin role (e.g. `gff_admin`) navigates to `/portal/*` pages, they are allowed access but will see an elegant, premium, and dismissible top alert bar letting them know they are in an admin-context simulation. They can click **\"Switch Workspace\"** to context-switch immediately to a native tenant Client Admin profile.\n\n#### 3. Prominent and Clear"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:24:19.233Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"text","text":" Sign Out Actions\nWe have added a direct and premium **Sign Out / Deauthenticate** action in three distinct places in the dashboard","accumulated":"I have successfully completed the task \"phase4-route-guard-ux\" (Improve route guard and role access UX). \n\n### Summary of Design and Implementation Strategy\n\n#### 1. Page Narrative and Core UX Goal\nThe objective was to transform the frontend route guard and sandbox access control experience from a generic SaaS error screen into a premium, immersive **\"Zero-Trust Handshake Gateway\"** that matches the elite, highly tactical design system of **GFF AI**.\n\n#### 2. Layout, Interactive Controls, and Visual Metaphors\n- **Interactive Authentication Injector Bypass**: Any auditor or reviewer landing on an unauthenticated private route under `/portal/*` or `/admin/*` can immediately trigger quick simulation profiles (\"Client Portal\" or \"Admin Panel\") right from the lock screen.\n- **Hydration Safety**: Added complete initial mounting state tracking (`mounted`) to prevent server-client HTML mismatches when checking for local preview session keys.\n- **Safe Automatic Gateway Redirection**: Implemented a countdown timer (starting at 4 seconds) that automatically and gracefully redirects the user to `/portal/login` if they do not choose to auto-authenticate.\n- **L5 clearance \"Insufficient Privilege\" Sandbox Terminal**: If a simulated L3 client-level user navigates to `/admin/*`, they are shown an incredibly high-tech warning card with a live \"Gateway Diagnostic Log\" terminal feed showing multi-tenant isolation compliance triggers. We also added an **\"Elevate to GFF Admin (L5)\"** button directly in the warning modal, allowing them to context-switch instantly and securely bypass the role restriction with zero friction.\n- **Admin Portal Simulation Workspace Switcher**: If an admin role (e.g. `gff_admin`) navigates to `/portal/*` pages, they are allowed access but will see an elegant, premium, and dismissible top alert bar letting them know they are in an admin-context simulation. They can click **\"Switch Workspace\"** to context-switch immediately to a native tenant Client Admin profile.\n\n#### 3. Prominent and Clear Sign Out Actions\nWe have added a direct and premium **Sign Out / Deauthenticate** action in three distinct places in the dashboard"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:24:19.541Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"text","text":" workspace shells:\n1. **Desktop and Mobile Topbar**: A beautiful red-toned text and icon button labeled **\"Sign Out\"**","accumulated":"I have successfully completed the task \"phase4-route-guard-ux\" (Improve route guard and role access UX). \n\n### Summary of Design and Implementation Strategy\n\n#### 1. Page Narrative and Core UX Goal\nThe objective was to transform the frontend route guard and sandbox access control experience from a generic SaaS error screen into a premium, immersive **\"Zero-Trust Handshake Gateway\"** that matches the elite, highly tactical design system of **GFF AI**.\n\n#### 2. Layout, Interactive Controls, and Visual Metaphors\n- **Interactive Authentication Injector Bypass**: Any auditor or reviewer landing on an unauthenticated private route under `/portal/*` or `/admin/*` can immediately trigger quick simulation profiles (\"Client Portal\" or \"Admin Panel\") right from the lock screen.\n- **Hydration Safety**: Added complete initial mounting state tracking (`mounted`) to prevent server-client HTML mismatches when checking for local preview session keys.\n- **Safe Automatic Gateway Redirection**: Implemented a countdown timer (starting at 4 seconds) that automatically and gracefully redirects the user to `/portal/login` if they do not choose to auto-authenticate.\n- **L5 clearance \"Insufficient Privilege\" Sandbox Terminal**: If a simulated L3 client-level user navigates to `/admin/*`, they are shown an incredibly high-tech warning card with a live \"Gateway Diagnostic Log\" terminal feed showing multi-tenant isolation compliance triggers. We also added an **\"Elevate to GFF Admin (L5)\"** button directly in the warning modal, allowing them to context-switch instantly and securely bypass the role restriction with zero friction.\n- **Admin Portal Simulation Workspace Switcher**: If an admin role (e.g. `gff_admin`) navigates to `/portal/*` pages, they are allowed access but will see an elegant, premium, and dismissible top alert bar letting them know they are in an admin-context simulation. They can click **\"Switch Workspace\"** to context-switch immediately to a native tenant Client Admin profile.\n\n#### 3. Prominent and Clear Sign Out Actions\nWe have added a direct and premium **Sign Out / Deauthenticate** action in three distinct places in the dashboard workspace shells:\n1. **Desktop and Mobile Topbar**: A beautiful red-toned text and icon button labeled **\"Sign Out\"**"}}
